        "Central Altadena": "Sitting directly at the base of the San Gabriel Mountains, just north of Pasadena, Altadena is an unincorporated area with a rich, fiercely independent history. Central Altadena serves as the heart of this foothills community. Unlike the dense urban grid of Los Angeles, Central Altadena is defined by its sweeping, tree-lined avenues (including the famous Christmas Tree Lane), large historic estates, deep residential lots, and a rugged, bohemian proximity to nature and hiking trails.",
