        "La La Land Pool Party Filming Location": "Residential property used for the pool party scene in the 2016 film La La Land.",
        "La La Land Someone in the Crowd House": "The private residence used for the iconic, color-drenched pool party sequence in the 2016 film La La Land.",
        "Los Encinos State Historic Park": "The site of a former ranch that served as a critical watering hole for travelers on El Camino Real, featuring original adobe structures.",
        "Old Nike Station LA-96C Radar Tower (Beneath Encino)": "Abandoned Nike missile radar station hidden in the Santa Monica Mountains above Encino.",
        "Rahad Jackson's House (Boogie Nights)": "The site of Boogie Nights' famously tense, botched drug deal involving firecrackers and the song Jessie's Girl. While the original 1964 home used for filming was completely remodeled in 2005, the address remains an infamous piece of cinematic history.",
        "San Vicente Mountain Park (Nike Missile Site LA-96C)": "Standing high above the Encino reservoir, this former Cold War anti-aircraft missile control site still features an imposing, rusty radar tower and concrete bunkers that visitors can climb for sweeping, 360-degree views of the sprawling city below.",
        "Sepulveda Basin Recreation Area (includes Balboa Park, Cricket Fields, Hjelte Sports Center)": "Park/Facility in Encino",
        "Sepulveda Dam": "A brutalist flood control basin offering expansive concrete vistas. Seen in Iron Man, Escape from New York, and The Fast and the Furious.",
        "Step Brothers House": "The exterior of the Brennan and Doback family home where Brenda and Robert move in together.",
