        "Adams Hill": "The History: A historic hillside neighborhood in Southeast Glendale known for its steep, winding roads and panoramic views of the San Fernando Valley and the Los Angeles basin.\n\nKey Features: It features an eclectic mix of Mid-Century Modern and Spanish-style homes. It is anchored by the landmark \"Adams Square,\" which houses a beautifully restored 1936 Streamline Moderne gas station that now serves as a community public art space.",
