        "DreamWorks Animation": "Perched like a sun-drenched Mediterranean villa, this stunning campus is the birthplace of Shrek, Kung Fu Panda, and How to Train Your Dragon. It serves as a high-tech sanctuary for artists, blending world-class technology with a campus that feels more like a creative retreat than a production house.",
        "Forest Lawn Memorial Park (Glendale)": "Beyond a cemetery, it is an architectural museum housing the Great Mausoleum, modeled after the Campo Santo in Genoa, and the \"Hall of the Crucifixion-Resurrection,\" one of the largest religious paintings in the world. (Forest Lawn Memorial Park)",
        "Former Tropico Library / Edward Weston Studio": "The History: Tropico has a surprising pedigree in fine art photography. In 1911, the seminal American photographer Edward Weston opened his first professional studio on Brand Boulevard in Tropico.\n\nThe Legacy: Weston\u2019s time in Tropico was incredibly productive; he began his career here before achieving international fame. For decades, the building also housed the Tropico branch of the Glendale Public Library, serving as a cultural anchor for the southern end of the city.",
