        "The Casa Adobe de San Rafael": "One of the oldest hidden gems in the county. Built in 1871 for the first Sheriff of Los Angeles County, it is a pristine example of Monterey Colonial architecture, offering a quiet, shaded retreat into the region\u2019s Spanish rancho past. (The Casa Adobe de San Rafael)",
        "The Derby House (Lloyd Wright)": "Designed by Lloyd Wright in 1926; utilizes geometric pre-cast concrete blocks to create a Mayan-inspired facade that integrates with the hillside.",
