        "Balboa Highlands HPOZ": "Architect: A. Quincy Jones, Frederick Emmons, and Claude Oakland\n\nDeveloper: Joseph Eichler\n\nArchitectural Style: Mid-Century Modern (Eichler)\n\nThe History: This is the only Joseph Eichler-developed tract in Los Angeles County. In 2010, it became the first post-WWII neighborhood in the San Fernando Valley to achieve Historic Preservation Overlay Zone (HPOZ) status.\n\nKey Architectural Features: The tract consists of roughly 100 homes defined by signature Eichler elements: floor-to-ceiling glass walls, open-air atriums at the center of the floor plan, and post-and-beam construction. The neighborhood features four distinct models with flat, A-frame, or slanted rooflines designed to create a seamless indoor-outdoor living experience.",
