        "Steve\u2019s Market (from the film Friday)": "The History: This humble neighborhood convenience store gained international pop-culture fame as a primary filming location for the 1995 cult classic film Friday. In the movie, it served as the corner store where characters Craig and Smokey would frequent.\n\nKey Features: While officially located just outside Gardena's city limits in the Harbor Gateway pocket, it is a must-see landmark for film buffs. It represents the \"everyday\" architecture of the South LA area that became globally recognizable through 90s cinema."
