        "Historic Pacific Boulevard Shopping District": "Heart of the historic Pacific Blvd shopping district.",
        "Santa Fe Avenue Industrial Corridor": "Fleabag motel featured as the Tiki Motel in \"The Terminator\".",
        "Saydel Inc.": "The Character: This \"surprisingly utilitarian\" wholesale store is a unique Los Angeles landmark, claiming to be the largest supplier of occult, spiritual, and New Age religious items worldwide.\n\nCultural Significance: For over 25 years, Saydel has served the city's diverse spiritual communities, carrying a vast array of Caribbean, Mexican, and African religious items. The interior is famous for its tidy, pharmacy-like rows of statues and candles representing Voodoo, Santeria, and Roman Catholic traditions.",
