        "Lincoln Heights Historic Preservation Overlay Zone": "The History: Recognized as a Historic Preservation Overlay Zone, Lincoln Heights holds the distinction of being considered Los Angeles's first true suburb, originally subdivided in the 1870s.\n\nNeighborhood Character: The HPOZ protects a dense and diverse collection of late 19th and early 20th-century residential architecture, including stunning Queen Anne, Craftsman, and Folk Victorian homes. It remains a deeply historic, working-class neighborhood that reflects the layered, multicultural history of the city's Eastside.",
