        "\u201cEl Paradiso\u201d (1964) \u2014 HCM #638": "The Vibe: This is a late-career masterpiece for Soriano. \"El Paradiso\" (The Paradise) is a rare example of a modernist hilltop villa in Monterey Park. It utilizes a radical, wide-span steel structure that allows for virtually no interior load-bearing walls.\n\nGazetteer Note: It represents the peak of Soriano\u2019s obsession with prefabrication. The house was designed to be easily replicated, though it remains a one-of-a-kind monument to his modular philosophy."
