        "Alvarado Terrace Historic District": "A residential street near a designated historic district known for its grand turn-of-the-century mansions.",
        "Angelus Rosedale Cemetery": "Founded in 1884, this is one of the oldest cemeteries in the city and notably the first in Los Angeles to be open to all races and creeds.",
        "Colby Poster Printing Co. (Former Site)": "Former site of Colby Poster Printing Company, a legendary LA poster printing operation that produced movie and concert posters for decades.",
        "Dino's Famous Chicken": "An iconic Los Angeles institution serving up legendary charbroiled chicken, renowned for its secret, bright red marinade and massive pile of french fries soaking up the juices. A true immigrant success story and an unpretentious culinary landmark.",
        "Doria Apartments (HCM #432)": "A three-and-a-half-story Mission Revival building built in 1905, designed by Gotfred Hanson for prominent community member Doria Deighton Jones.",
