        "Micheltorena Stairs": "A steep public stairway famous for its vibrant heart and rainbow murals that have become a symbol of Silver Lake's colorful, bohemian identity. The stairs provide a direct hillside route between Sunset Boulevard and the high ridges of the neighborhood, offering a lung-burning climb rewarded at the summit by views of the Silver Lake Reservoir and, on clear days, the San Gabriel Mountains beyond. Part of the original network of pedestrian infrastructure built to connect early 20th-century residents to the streetcar lines below.",
