        "N-HN House": "Modernist residential design on Berkeley Circle.",
        "Neutra VDL Studio and Residences": "The home and studio of pioneering Austrian-American architect Richard Neutra, and a National Historic Landmark. Built on the edge of the Silver Lake Reservoir, the VDL Research House embodies Neutra's philosophy of \"biorealism\" \u2014 the idea that architecture should blur the boundary between interior and exterior through massive windows, rooftop gardens, and a deep responsiveness to light, water, and landscape. The building is widely credited as the crucible of the \"Silver Lake style\" of light-filled, hillside modernist living that has defined the neighborhood's architectural identity ever since. Now managed by Cal Poly Pomona, it is open for public tours.",
        "Olive Motel": "Classic motel on Sunset Blvd.",
        "Oliver House (HCM #442)": "Designed by Rudolph Schindler; known for its complex interlocking volumes and hillside integration.",
        "ON Klub (Former Mod Scene Club)": "Former site of the ON Klub, a legendary Mod scene nightclub.",
        "Park Imperial (Fake Japanese Style)": "Apartment complex with faux Japanese architectural styling.",
        "Perling Mural": "Local public mural on Hyperion Ave.",
        "Philip Lumbang Mural (Controversy Site)": "Site of the Philip Lumbang mural that sparked a neighborhood controversy over public art and gentrification.",
        "Reiner-Burchill (Silvertop)": "Iconic modernist house designed by John Lautner.",
        "Rene Faron Residence (Paul R. Williams)": "Residential design by legendary Black architect Paul R. Williams.",
        "Russian Orthodox Cathedral Viewpoint": "Elevated viewpoint on Ellsworth St offering views of the Holy Virgin Mary Russian Orthodox Cathedral.",
        "Sachs Apartments / Manola Court (R.M. Schindler)": "Multi-unit residential complex designed by R.M. Schindler.",
        "Schindler's How House": "Residential design by R.M. Schindler on Silver Ridge Ave.",
        "Schrage Hallauer House (Raphael Soriano)": "Residential design by influential modernist architect Raphael Soriano.",
        "Silver Lake Art House (Mermaid and Cow)": "Residential art house featuring distinctive mermaid and cow sculptures and folk art exterior.",
        "Silver Lake Community Church": "Local community church on Hyperion Ave.",
        "Silver Lake Creative Corridor": "Situated near the historic Hyperion Bridge and the former site of Walt Disney's first major studio, this area is a long-standing center for LA's artistic community.",
        "Silver Lake Recreation Center": "Park/Facility in Silver Lake",
        "Silver Lake Residents Association Mural": "Community mural on Silver Lake Blvd.",
        "Silverlake Branch Library": "Modern public library with a wide collection and public computers.",
        "Silverlake Car Wash (Googie Architecture)": "Car wash featuring Googie-style mid-century modern architecture on Beverly Blvd.",
        "Silverlake Dog Park": "Park/Facility in Silver Lake",
        "Silverlake Palms": "Residential complex on Silver Lake Blvd.",
        "Site LA (Former Arts Residency)": "Former arts residency and exhibition space on Sunset Blvd.",
        "Skinner House (William Kesling)": "Residential design by Silver Lake modernist architect William Kesling.",
        "Sokol House (HCM #1157)": "Another standout from the Richard Neutra 'Colony' series overlooking the reservoir. Features striking views of the Silver Lake Reservoir and signature mitered glass corners.",
        "Southall House (HCM #893)": "A Rudolph Schindler project for an artist; features a unique modular design with high clerestory windows.",
        "Space Invader Mural (Sunset Coin-Op Laundry)": "Street art Space Invader mosaic mural on the exterior of Sunset Coin-Op Laundry.",
        "St. Teresa of Avila Church": "Catholic church on Fargo St in Silver Lake.",
        "Static Medium Building (Dabs Myla Mural)": "Building featuring a large-scale mural by renowned street artists Dabs Myla.",
        "Sun Lake Drugs (Historic Neon)": "Pharmacy with a notable surviving vintage neon sign on Sunset Blvd.",
        "Swan Stairs": "A lush, hidden staircase that captures the bohemian, naturalistic character of the Silver Lake hills.",
        "T.V. Graveyard Site": "Former site of the T.V. Graveyard, a legendary outdoor art installation.",
        "The Chandelier Tree": "Hidden in plain sight on a quiet Silver Lake residential street, this massive, century-old sycamore tree has been adorned with dozens of vintage, fully wired chandeliers by a local artist, creating a magical, glowing spectacle for anyone driving by at night.",
        "The Dov Charney Mansion": "The massive 12,000-square-foot Silver Lake estate of the American Apparel founder, known for its brutalist architecture and expansive views.",
        "The Foot Clinic": "Local podiatry clinic on Sunset Blvd.",
        "The Frog Pond / Lyric Hyperion": "Currently operating as the Lyric Hyperion Theatre & Cafe, this building holds a vital place in Los Angeles LGBTQ+ history. During the 1970s and 80s, the space operated as 'The Frog Pond', a highly popular gay restaurant and cabaret. In 1980, the establishment was firebombed by an anti-gay assailant. The tragic blast injured three people and served as a major catalyst for the community; in direct response, the Sunset Junction Neighborhood Alliance was formed to ease neighborhood tensions and promote unity, eventually launching the famous Sunset Junction Street Fair.",
        "The Manual Archives (Puppetry)": "Archive and workshop dedicated to the art of puppetry.",
        "Tiki-Ti": "Legendary historic tiki bar opened in 1961 by Ray Buhen, one of the original bartenders at Don the Beachcomber.",
        "Tokio Florist / Sakai-Kozawa": "Historic former florist and residence notable for its Japanese-American heritage.",
        "Tommy Lasorda Field of Dreams": "Park/Facility in Silver Lake / Echo Park",
        "VietSoy": "Vietnamese-soy fusion restaurant on Hyperion Ave.",
        "Waverly Drive Apartment Complex": "Apartment complex on Waverly Dr.",
        "Westerly Terrace Viewpoint": "Notable hillside viewpoint in Silver Lake."
