        "Frank Gehry Wells Fargo Branch": "A Wells Fargo branch designed by the world-renowned architect Frank Gehry (completed in 1982). It is a celebrated example of deconstructivist architecture, designed to look like a fragmented \"drawing of a building\" with a fa\u00e7ade that appears to balance precariously.",
        "NoHo Arts District North": "A residential and commercial transition area near the North Hollywood park and the historic Amelia Earhart Library.",
        "Papoo's Hot Dog Show (Site)": "Long-standing neighborhood institution famous for its historic signage and iconic 'thinker' statue. Now demolished.",
        "Paty's Restaurant": "Home to Paty\u2019s Restaurant, a legendary neighborhood diner since 1960. It is a world-famous celebrity hangout (regularly visited by stars like Frank Sinatra and Bob Hope) and is known for its \"Green Room\" where major Hollywood deals have been signed. It also served as a filming location for The Office (the site of Jan and Dwight's secret meeting) and Desperate Housewives.",
        "The 40-Year-Old Virgin Apartment": "The exterior filming location for Andy Stitzer's apartment in the 2005 Judd Apatow film.",
