        "Buster Keaton & Natalie Talmadge Residence": "The Italian Renaissance-style former home of silent comedy genius Buster Keaton and actress Natalie Talmadge. It is a testament to the sheer concentration of early film stars who lived in the historic West Adams district.",
        "Club Fais Do-Do": "Historic West Adams music venue on W Adams Blvd.",
